### 1.2 Yellowstone gRPC – Vollständige Datenpunkte aus geyser.proto

**A) SHRED-EBENE (Ultra-Low-Latency, Pre-Block)**
```
- slot_index:          uint64   – Slot-Nummer
- shred_index:         uint32   – Position im Block-Aufbau
- shred_type:          enum     – DATA | CODE (Reed-Solomon)
- shred_size:          uint32   – Bytes (typisch: ~1280 Bytes)
- arrival_nanos:       int64    – Ankunftszeit in Nanosekunden
- is_last_in_slot:     bool     – Letzter Shred des Slots?
```

**B) TRANSAKTIONS-EBENE**
```
- signature:           [u8; 64]       – TX-Signatur
- account_keys:        Vec<Pubkey>    – Alle beteiligten Accounts
- instructions:        Vec<Instruction>
  - program_id:        Pubkey         – Welches Programm (DEX, Lending, etc.)
  - accounts:          Vec<u8>        – Account-Indizes
  - data:              Vec<u8>        – Instruction-Data (hex)
- compute_units_consumed: u64         – Tatsächlich verbrauchte CU
- compute_units_requested: u64        – Angeforderte CU (SetComputeUnitLimit)
- compute_unit_price:  u64            – Priorität in Microlamports/CU
- log_messages:        Vec<String>    – Output der Programmausführung
- pre_token_balances:  Vec<TokenBalance>
- post_token_balances: Vec<TokenBalance>
- pre_balances:        Vec<u64>       – SOL-Balances vor TX
- post_balances:       Vec<u64>       – SOL-Balances nach TX
- err:                 Option<Error>  – None = Success
- fee:                 u64            – Basisgebühr in Lamports
- recent_blockhash:    Hash
- version:             Legacy | v0
- address_lookup_tables: Vec<ALT>
```

**C) ACCOUNT-EBENE**
```
- pubkey:              Pubkey
- lamports:            u64            – SOL-Balance
- owner:               Pubkey         – Besitzerprogramm
- executable:          bool
- rent_epoch:          u64
- data:                Vec<u8>        – Account-Daten (Rohdaten)
- write_version:       u64            – Version bei Write-Lock
- slot:                u64
- is_startup:          bool
```

**D) BLOCK-EBENE**
```
- slot:                u64
- blockhash:           Hash
- rewards:             Vec<Reward>    – Leader-Belohnungen
- block_time:          i64            – Unix-Timestamp
- block_height:        u64
- parent_slot:         u64
- transactions:        Vec<Transaction>
- entry_count:         u64
```

